      • initialize

        public abstract boolean initialize(@NonNull
                                   Lookup context,
                                   @NonNull
                                   AtomicBoolean cancel)
        Initialize this scope provider with the supplied context.
        Parameters:
        context - a Lookup defining the context
        cancel - set to true if initialization should be canceled
        Returns:
        true if this scope is usable for the supplied context, false otherwise

      • getScope

        @CheckForNull
public abstract Scope getScope()
        Get this provider's scope. The scope can be null if this provider is not yet initialized, or this provider is not usable for the supplied context.
        Returns:
        the Scope
        See Also:
        initialize(org.openide.util.Lookup, java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean)

      • getIcon

        @CheckForNull
public Icon getIcon()
        Override this method if the icon should be different depending on the context.
        Returns:
        an icon for the Scope, or null if the default should be used.
        See Also:
        initialize(org.openide.util.Lookup, java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean), ScopeDescription

      • getDetail

        @CheckForNull
public String getDetail()
        Override this method if an explaining string should be displayed behind the scope's name. This is used for scopes like "- Current File (Filename.java)".
        Returns:
        an explaining string, or null of nothing should be displayed.

      • getProblem

        @CheckForNull
public Problem getProblem()
        Override this method if a problem can occur when the user selects this scope. This is used for scopes like "- Open Projects with Dependencies", when searching for constants.
        Returns:
        a problem with an explaining string, or null of nothing should be displayed.
        Since:
        1.44
